The paper discusses a new approach for semantic information extraction from unstructured web sources, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The approach is ontology-driven and employs Answer Set Programming, which are techniques commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the integration of existing IE techniques, which could fall under the category of Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the positive feedback from business customers, indicating that the approach has practical applications, which could fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
